comment: Favors (UTA) establishes a legal screening position in Murray's (SAS) path. Since he is stationary and in view, he does not have to give him room to avoid the screen.
[Observable in enhanced video] Mitchell (UTA) slides his pivot foot slightly at the end of his dribble.
Murray (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position on Mitchell's (UTA) shot attempt near the rim, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Green (SAS) makes arm contact with Favors (UTA) and affects his shot attempt near the rim. 01:38.1 01:38.1
Green (SAS) and Crowder (UTA) engage and disengage off-ball.
Crowder (UTA) maintains a legal guarding position on Green's (SAS) jump shot attempt. 01:27.1 01:27.1
After communicating with the Replay Center, the decision on the floor that the shot attempt was taken behind the three-point line is confirmed.
Favors (UTA) establishes a screening position in Murray's (SAS) path, but readjusts his position and does not give Murray a chance to go around the screen.
LATR shows Murray (SAS) legally contests Mitchell's (UTA) drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Ginobili (SAS) clamps Favors (UTA), affecting his ability to secure the rebound.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it is confirmed that Favors (UTA) makes contact with the ball last before it goes out of bounds. 01:11.1 01:11.1
Ingles (UTA) and Mills (SAS) collide off-ball while performing normal basketball moves, and the contact is deemed incidental.
Gasol (SAS) establishes a legal screening position in Ingles' (UTA) path and absorbs the contact. After the screen, Ingles attempts to go through Gasol and the players engage and then disengage.
Mitchell (UTA) cleanly steals the ball from Anderson (SAS). Period 00:59.8 00:59.8
Gasol (SAS) establishes a legal screening position in Ingles' (UTA) path and absorbs the contact.

[Observable in enhanced video] After his jump stop, Anderson (SAS) slides his left pivot foot slightly before jumping off his right foot. He releases the ball before returning his pivot foot to the floor.
Anderson (SAS) draws Favors (UTA) into the air towards him with a pump fake. Favors lands on Anderson's foot, affecting his shooting motion.
Angle RATR - Ingles (UTA) makes arm contact with Anderson (SAS) that affects ability to control the ball. 00:47.2 00:47.2
Favors (UTA) establishes a screening position in Green's (SAS) path before the contact. 00:39.3 00:39.3
Gasol (SAS) establishes a screening position on O'Neale (UTA) and is firming up when O'Neale passes, with almost no contact to his body. Once O'Neale has passed, Gasol is legally in his path.
O'Neale (UTA) makes marginal contact with Ginobili (SAS) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Favors (UTA) makes contact with the ball on Ginobili's (SAS) driving shot attempt. And contact to Ginobili's arm after the ball is knocked loose is deemed marginal. 00:22.6 00:22.6
Anderson (SAS) commits a take foul on Mitchell (UTA). 00:16.8 00:16.8

[Observable in enhanced video] Ginobili (SAS) gathers on his left foot and takes a long, legal step back with his right foot to establish his pivot foot when he stops. He slides his pivot slightly before he passes.
O'Neale (UTA) maintains legal guarding position against Ginobili (SAS) during his drive.
Anderson (SAS) pump fakes and draws O'Neale (UTA) towards him. O'Neale stops and reestablishes a floor position before Anderson initiates contact and then loses the ball.

Based on all available angles, Anderson's (SAS) left foot is inbounds when he touches the ball while it is still in the air. He redirects it inbounds before he steps out of bounds with his right foot.

RATR shows Ingles (UTA) initiates contact to Ginobili's (SAS) back, extending his arms and dislodging him as he retrieves the loose ball. Event Assessments: CC = Correct Call, IC = Incorrect Call, CNC = Correct Non-Call, INC = Incorrect Non-Call
